<HEADLINE>
RECIPE-CRABS-HNS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STUFFED CRABS -- 1 dozen boiled crabs 4 tablespoons butter,
divided use 1/2 cup minced onion 1/4 cup minced celery 1/4 cup
minced bell pepper 2 cloves garlic, minced 2 tablespoons finely
chopped parsley 1 egg, beaten 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon
pepper 1/2 teaspoon Creole seasoning 1 tablespoon lemon juice 1
1/4 cups seasoned bread crumbs, divided use
</P>
<P>
Pick crabs, saving meat and fat. Clean the back shells of 6 to 8
crabs, depending on size, discarding all else. Set aside.
</P>
<P>
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large,
heavy skillet and saute onion, celery and bell pepper until soft.
Add garlic and saute briefly.
</P>
<P>
In medium bowl, mix crabmeat and fat, parsley, egg, onion
mixture, salt, pepper, Creole seasoning, lemon juice and 1 cup
bread crumbs.
</P>
<P>
Divide into 6 to 8 portions. Stuff mixture into shells and top
with remaining bread crumbs. Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons of
butter, cut into bits.
</P>
<P>
Bake until stuffed crabs are nicely browned, about 20 to 30
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Approximate nutritional values per
serving: 160 calories (43.3 percent calories from fat), 9 g
protein, 13 g carbohydrate, 1 g sugar, 1 g dietary fiber, 8 g
fat, 65 mg cholesterol, 640 mg sodium.
</P>
